quran[71]{c,v,t}:
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,because the blind man came to him
  80,3,But how do you know? Perhaps he would be purified
  80,4,"or reminded, and the reminder benefit him"
  80,5,As for him who thinks himself self-sufficient
  80,6,you give him your complete attention
  80,7,but it is not up to you whether or not he is purified
  80,8,But as for him who comes to you eagerly
  80,9,showing fearfulness
  80,10,from him you are distracted
  80,11,No indeed! Truly it is a reminder
  80,12,and whoever wills pays heed to it
  80,13,Inscribed on Honoured Pages
  80,14,"exalted, purified"
  80,15,by the hands of scribes
  80,16,"noble, virtuous"
  80,17,Curse man for his ingratitude
  80,18,From what thing did He create him
  80,19,From a drop of sperm He created him and proportioned him
  80,20,Then He eases the way for him
  80,21,Then He causes him to die and buries him
  80,22,"Then, when He wills, He raises him from the dead"
  80,23,No indeed! He has not done what He ordered him
  80,24,Man has only to look at his food
  80,25,We pour down plentiful water
  80,26,then split the earth into furrows
  80,27,Then We make grain grow in it
  80,28,and grapes and herbs
  80,29,and olives and dates
  80,30,and luxuriant gardens
  80,31,and orchards and meadows
  80,32,for you and your livestock to enjoy
  80,33,When the Deafening Blast comes
  80,34,the Day a man will flee from his brother
  80,35,and his mother and his father
  80,36,and his wife and his children
  80,37,on that Day every man among them will have concerns enough of his own
  80,38,That Day some faces will be radiant
  80,39,"laughing, rejoicing"
  80,40,That Day some faces will be dust-covered
  80,41,overcast with gloom
  80,42,Those are the dissolute kafirun
  81,1,When the sun is compacted in blackness
  81,2,when the stars fall in rapid succession
  81,3,when the mountains are set in motion
  81,4,when the camels in foal are neglected
  81,5,when the wild beasts are all herded together
  81,6,when the oceans surge into each other
  81,7,when the selves are arranged into classes
  81,8,when the baby girl buried alive is asked
  81,9,for what crime she was killed
  81,10,when the Pages are opened up
  81,11,when the Heaven is peeled away
  81,12,when the Fire is set ablaze
  81,13,when the Garden is brought up close
  81,14,then each self will know what it has done
  81,15,No! I swear by the planets with their retrograde motion
  81,16,"swiftly moving, self-concealing"
  81,17,and by the night when it draws in
  81,18,and by the dawn when it exhales
  81,19,truly it is the speech of a noble Messenger
  81,20,"possessing great strength, securely placed with the Lord of the Throne"
  81,21,"obeyed there, trustworthy"
  81,22,Your companion is not mad
  81,23,He saw him on the clear horizon
  81,24,Nor is he miserly with the Unseen
  81,25,Nor is it the word of an accursed Shaytan
  81,26,"So where, then, are you going"
  81,27,It is nothing but a Reminder to all the worlds
  81,28,to whoever among you wishes to go straight
  81,29,"But you will not will unless Allah wills, the Lord of all the Worlds"